The paper presents a visualization tool for browsing and searching through large-scale machine learning datasets, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the tool is built on top of the VizWiz dataset, which is a multimodal dataset of images and text collected from blind and visually impaired users, indicating potential relevance to natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
